---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const updated = "June 28, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="cookie notice - embody.tools"
  description="The complete, honest list of cookies embody.tools uses. Spoiler: only the strictly-necessary ones, no tracking, and that's why there's no cookie banner."
>
  <section class="page-section legal-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">cookies</p>
    <h1>cookie notice</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Most cookie banners exist because the site behind them is tracking you. This one
      isn&rsquo;t, so there&rsquo;s no banner &mdash; just this page, which lists every
      cookie we use and why. We set no advertising or cross-site tracking cookies, full
      stop.
    </p>
    <p class="legal-updated mono">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </section>

  <article class="page-section tight legal-body">
    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      Under EU and UK law you only have to ask for consent before setting cookies that
      aren&rsquo;t <strong>strictly necessary</strong> &mdash; the analytics, advertising,
      and tracking kind. We don&rsquo;t use any of those. The only cookies in play keep you
      signed in and keep the site secure, our analytics is cookieless, and our fonts are
      served from our own domain. That&rsquo;s why you don&rsquo;t get a pop-up asking you
      to &ldquo;accept all.&rdquo;
    </p>

    <h2>What we actually set</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>A session cookie</strong> &mdash; set only after you sign in, so the site
        recognizes you on the next request. It&rsquo;s issued by
        <a href="https://www.better-auth.com/">Better Auth</a>, marked HttpOnly and Secure
        (so it can&rsquo;t be read by scripts and only travels over HTTPS), and it clears
        when you sign out or it expires. If you never sign in, it&rsquo;s never set.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare security cookies</strong> &mdash; Cloudflare protects and
        delivers the site, and may set its own strictly-necessary cookies (such as
        <span class="mono">__cf_bm</span>) to tell humans from bots. These are short-lived,
        hold no personal profile, and aren&rsquo;t used to track you across sites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A Turnstile check</strong> &mdash; when you contribute a specimen,
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/products/turnstile/">Cloudflare Turnstile</a>
        runs a background challenge to confirm you&rsquo;re human. It may store a
        short-lived token strictly to run that security check, not to profile you.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don&rsquo;t set</h2>
    <p>
      No advertising cookies. No cross-site tracking cookies. No analytics cookies. No
      &ldquo;social&rdquo; pixels. We don&rsquo;t sell or share your data, and there are no
      third-party trackers embedded anywhere on this site.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics without cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a> to
      see aggregate page traffic. It is <strong>cookieless</strong> by design: it sets no
      cookie, stores no client-side state, doesn&rsquo;t fingerprint your device, and
      collects no personal data. If the analytics token isn&rsquo;t configured for a given
      deployment, the beacon isn&rsquo;t even loaded.
    </p>

    <h2>Fonts and embeds</h2>
    <p>
      Our display font (Inter) is <strong>self-hosted</strong> on this domain, so loading
      the site doesn&rsquo;t send your IP address to a third-party font CDN. Specimen
      thumbnails and other images are served through Cloudflare. None of this sets a cookie
      on your browser.
    </p>

    <h2>Your controls</h2>
    <p>
      You can block or delete cookies in your browser settings at any time &mdash; if you
      block the session cookie you simply won&rsquo;t be able to stay signed in. Signing out
      clears the session immediately. Because we don&rsquo;t track you, there&rsquo;s nothing
      for a &ldquo;Do Not Track&rdquo; or &ldquo;Global Privacy Control&rdquo; signal to turn
      off &mdash; but we honor the spirit of both regardless.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-sign mono">
      More detail is in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
